"use strict";(self.webpackChunktexter_docs=self.webpackChunktexter_docs||[]).push([[6367],{50162:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/2026/05/16/airtable-adapter-doc-corrections","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/16/airtable-adapter-doc-corrections","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-16-airtable-adapter-doc-corrections.md","title":"Airtable Adapter + Adapter Doc Corrections","description":"A new Airtable adapter page, plus an audit pass over the existing adapter docs to fix a handful of inaccuracies caught against the live server code.","date":"2026-05-16T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Airtable Adapter + Adapter Doc Corrections","date":"2026-05-16T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters","docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Templates Export + Partner Bundles","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/15/templates-export-partner-bundles"}},"content":"A new Airtable adapter page, plus an audit pass over the existing adapter docs to fix a handful of inaccuracies caught against the live server code.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Airtable adapter** \u2014 full documentation for `getCustomerDetails`, `newOpportunity` / `createRecord`, and `updateRecord`, including the required `crmConfig` (`baseId`, `tableId`, `viewId`, `authToken`, `phoneColumn`), per-call overrides for base/table/view, and notes on the auto-injected phone column.\\n- **Rapid `crmGetFields`** \u2014 undocumented op that returns the hardcoded Hebrew status list used by Texter\'s `changeStatus` dropdowns.\\n- **Senzey `crmConfig`** \u2014 config table (`server`, `username`, `password`) was missing from the page; now included.\\n- **Tazman `crmConfig`** \u2014 config table (`server`, `token`, plus the four `result*Field` overrides) was missing from the page; now included.\\n\\n## Fixed\\n\\n- **Rapid `crmGetAppointments`** \u2014 `datesRangeTo` is a window **length** in days, not an end-day index (`0, 14` searches today through 14 days out).\\n- **Rapid `crmCreateAppointment`** \u2014 result is `crmData.appointmentId` (string), not an array.\\n- **Rapid `uploadFile`** \u2014 result now documents `crmData.uploadedFile` shape.\\n- **Rapid `closeTicket`** \u2014 returns `on_failure` when `crmData.cardCode` is missing (was vaguely worded).\\n- **Senzey `getCustomerDetails`** \u2014 `deepLink` is only set when `user_type` is `2` or `3`; the adapter always sends `incl_pclient=TRUE` so both clients and potential clients are searched.\\n- **GoogleSheet `getCustomerDetails`** \u2014 dashed phone variant assumes Israeli format; raw CSV columns spread onto `crmData` after mapped fields can overwrite `name` / `phone` / `id` / `status` if column headers collide.\\n- **Powerlink** \u2014 `showDuplicates` fires on a single contact-fallback match too (not only on multi-account matches); `displayExistingData` writes `accountid` (lowercase) regardless of the config-key casing; `setOwner` failure conditions documented.\\n- **Provet** \u2014 removed the `closeTicket` section; the op is effectively a no-op that doesn\'t call Provet at all.\\n- **Lead.IM** \u2014 display-mode edge case where `crmData` exists without `aid`/`lid` (or `pp_aid`/`pp_lid`) still returns success but with no `id` and a bare-base `deepLink`.\\n- **Salesforce `getCustomerDetails`** \u2014 warned that `contactObjectCustomFields` is a **total replacement** of the default field list, so omitting `Id` / `AccountId` / `Name` / etc. silently drops the corresponding `crmData` keys; `crmData.Accounts` is a numeric-keyed object, not an array.\\n- **Zoho** \u2014 `orgId` is optional (only used to build `deepLink`); documented `fieldsOverride` and its total-replacement caveat; clarified that an empty-row query returns `success: true` with `crmData.queryResult: {}`, not `on_failure`."},{"id":"/2026/05/15/templates-export-partner-bundles","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/15/templates-export-partner-bundles","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-15-templates-export-partner-bundles.md","title":"Templates Export + Partner Bundles","description":"The Templates page picks up Export, three Partner Bundle starter sets, Draft mode, and inline editing of bundled templates \u2014 among a stack of UX fixes.","date":"2026-05-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Templates Export + Partner Bundles","date":"2026-05-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","docs","site"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Airtable Adapter + Adapter Doc Corrections","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/16/airtable-adapter-doc-corrections"},"nextItem":{"title":"Unsubscribe Phones + Bot Recipes","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/15/unsubscribe-phones-bot-recipes"}},"content":"The Templates page picks up Export, three Partner Bundle starter sets, Draft mode, and inline editing of bundled templates \u2014 among a stack of UX fixes.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Export mode** \u2014 new tab that downloads every WhatsApp template from a Texter account as JSON, either as a `<projectId>_templates.json` file or printed inline for copy-paste.\\n- **Partner Bundles** \u2014 third input mode that opens a picker for pre-built starter sets: **Rapid** (15 templates for clinics on Rapid), **Optima** (5 templates for dental clinics on Optima), and **CPA Assist** (2 templates for accounting offices). Tick a bundle or individual templates, hit Save.\\n- **Inline template editing** \u2014 each partner template can be expanded in the picker to edit title / name / body before importing.\\n- **Seed input for Optima** \u2014 single field above the templates that string-replaces every `\u05e9\u05dd \u05d4\u05e7\u05dc\u05d9\u05e0\u05d9\u05e7\u05d4` placeholder across the selected templates on Save.\\n- **Draft mode** \u2014 submit-mode toggle that creates + localizes templates without submitting for WhatsApp approval, so they stay editable in the Texter UI.\\n- **Paste JSON mode** \u2014 alternative to file upload; parses on each keystroke.\\n- **Per-call progress + error summary** \u2014 bars advance per API call (not per template), with a configurable delay between every call to dodge rate limits and an end-of-run errors list naming each failure.\\n- **Help tooltips** \u2014 every config field shows a `?` button with field-specific guidance, including the required Texter API scope.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **URL** \u2014 slug is now `/docs/templates-import-export`. Old `/templates-import` and `/docs/tools/template-json-import` redirect.\\n- **Progress UI** \u2014 outcome-driven colors (green / orange / red / striped grey), and the Result/Progress card height tracks the form card so the bottoms stay aligned."},{"id":"/2026/05/15/unsubscribe-phones-bot-recipes","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/15/unsubscribe-phones-bot-recipes","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-15-unsubscribe-phones-bot-recipes.md","title":"Unsubscribe Phones + Bot Recipes","description":"A new in-browser tool to bulk-unsubscribe phone numbers from a Texter environment, plus a \\"Bot Recipes\\" section under Bot YAML with copy-paste-ready snippets for common starter bots.","date":"2026-05-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Unsubscribe Phones + Bot Recipes","date":"2026-05-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","docs","yaml","site"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Templates Export + Partner Bundles","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/15/templates-export-partner-bundles"},"nextItem":{"title":"Template JSON import in Tools","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/14/template-json-import"}},"content":"A new in-browser tool to bulk-unsubscribe phone numbers from a Texter environment, plus a \\"Bot Recipes\\" section under Bot YAML with copy-paste-ready snippets for common starter bots.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Unsubscribe Phones** \u2014 new tool at [Tools \u2192 Unsubscribe Phones](/docs/tools/unsubscribe-phones) for bulk-unsubscribing phone numbers from a Texter environment. Paste a comma-separated list or upload a CSV (`phone` column), capped at 5,000 per request. Pre-flight probe aborts on auth / config / unreachable-instance errors with one clear message; otherwise the result panel shows per-number outcomes with HTTP status and reason.\\n- **Bot Recipes** \u2014 new section under Bot YAML with copy-paste-ready snippets for common starter bots: **AI Bot** (external-bot wiring + `AI_TEST` command), **CPA Assist Bot** (mandatory CPA Assist starter, includes the nodes routed by partner templates), **Optima Bot** (meeting-reminder webhook handler), and **Handoff Only Bot** (forward everything to a human)."},{"id":"/2026/05/14/template-json-import","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/14/template-json-import","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-14-template-json-import.md","title":"Template JSON import in Tools","description":"A new in-browser flow under Bot documentation \u2192 Tools uploads provider template JSON and runs create \u2192 localizations \u2192 submit against the Texter API v2 from your machine.","date":"2026-05-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Template JSON import in Tools","date":"2026-05-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","docs","site"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Unsubscribe Phones + Bot Recipes","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/15/unsubscribe-phones-bot-recipes"},"nextItem":{"title":"Set Display Name Func Docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/13/set-display-name"}},"content":"A new in-browser flow under **Bot documentation \u2192 Tools** uploads provider template JSON and runs create \u2192 localizations \u2192 submit against the Texter API v2 from your machine.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Template JSON import** \u2014 page at [Templates Import / Export](/docs/templates-import-export): enter project ID, API key, and WhatsApp account ID; upload JSON (array of templates, a `templates` wrapper, or a single object); optional keep-names, suffix, and delay between creates; live log and per-phase summary. Old `/templates-import` URLs redirect here."},{"id":"/2026/05/13/set-display-name","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/13/set-display-name","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-13-set-display-name.md","title":"Set Display Name Func Docs","description":"The YAML reference now documents the new setDisplayName chat func \u2014 sets a custom chat title (stored separately from the channel-provided %chat:title%), with optional length capping and overflow handling.","date":"2026-05-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Set Display Name Func Docs","date":"2026-05-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Template JSON import in Tools","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/14/template-json-import"},"nextItem":{"title":"Subscription Scenarios + Data Storage Docs Polish","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/13/subscription-scenarios-docs-polish"}},"content":"The YAML reference now documents the new **`setDisplayName`** chat func \u2014 sets a custom chat title (stored separately from the channel-provided `%chat:title%`), with optional length capping and overflow handling.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Set Display Name** \u2014 new page under `Func / Chat` covering `setDisplayName`: required `displayName`, plus optional `setOnlyIfEmpty`, `maxLength` (1\u2013255), and `onOverflow` (`truncate` / `skip` / `fail`). Examples include setting from collected first+last name, only-if-empty (don\'t clobber WhatsApp profile names), CRM-lookup with cap, strict-fail for re-prompt flows, and clearing the value.\\n\\n## Fixed\\n\\n- **YAML Overview** \u2014 chat row now lists `setDisplayName`; the `dataStorage` row uses the real `func_id`s (`get` / `set` / `list` / `delete`) instead of the stale `getData` / `setData` / `listData` / `deleteData` labels."},{"id":"/2026/05/13/subscription-scenarios-docs-polish","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/13/subscription-scenarios-docs-polish","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-13-subscription-scenarios-docs-polish.md","title":"Subscription Scenarios + Data Storage Docs Polish","description":"Ten new (SUB) webhook scenarios cover the full chat lifecycle \u2014 pending, resolved (with by-agent / by-bot variants), labels, external bot toggles, and channel health \u2014 so you can subscribe an external system to any of them via a single webhook. The newly-added Data Storage and updateCrmData docs are refined to match the rest of the Func reference style, with worked before/after examples for every mergingMode.","date":"2026-05-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"scenarios","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/scenarios"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Subscription Scenarios + Data Storage Docs Polish","date":"2026-05-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["scenarios","automation","docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Set Display Name Func Docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/13/set-display-name"},"nextItem":{"title":"Data Storage Funcs + Chat `updateCrmData` Docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/12/data-storage-update-crm"}},"content":"Ten new **(SUB)** webhook scenarios cover the full chat lifecycle \u2014 pending, resolved (with by-agent / by-bot variants), labels, external bot toggles, and channel health \u2014 so you can subscribe an external system to any of them via a single webhook. The newly-added Data Storage and `updateCrmData` docs are refined to match the rest of the Func reference style, with worked before/after examples for every `mergingMode`.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **(SUB) Chat Pending** \u2014 webhook fires when a chat moves to pending (waiting for a human agent).\\n- **(SUB) Chat Resolved** \u2014 webhook on any resolution, with the full chat payload.\\n- **(SUB) Chat Resolved by Agent** \u2014 same as above, filtered to human-driven resolutions only (`exists(agent.uid)`).\\n- **(SUB) Chat Resolved by Bot** \u2014 bot/auto-resolve only.\\n- **(SUB) Chat Labels Updated** \u2014 fires whenever labels change on a chat, with the new label set.\\n- **(SUB) Specific Label Added** \u2014 narrower variant that only fires for one configured label.\\n- **(SUB) External Bot Enabled** / **Disabled** \u2014 pair of webhooks for `externalBot` flips, useful for AI handoff observability.\\n- **(SUB) Channel Health Problem Created** / **Resolved** \u2014 alert/recovery pair for channel health events.\\n- **New trigger labels** \u2014 `Channel Health Recovered` and `Chat Labels Updated` added to the marketplace display map, with matching icons.\\n- **`on-pending` / `on-labels` scenario tags** \u2014 registered in the `add-scenario` skill taxonomy so future scenarios can reuse them.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **`updateCrmData` docs** \u2014 full rewrite to match the Func reference style. Each `mergingMode` (`replace`, `assign`, `merge`, `defaults`, `defaultsDeep`) now has a worked **Before / After** JSON example showing exactly what survives and what doesn\'t, plus a dedicated \\"reset `crmData` completely\\" example. `merge` is called out as the default.\\n- **Data Storage Overview** \u2014 restructured as a short concept page: the four functions (`get` / `set` / `list` / `delete`), the `collection` + `key` model, output paths on `%state:node.<name>%`, TTL rules, and a single Limits table.\\n- **`get` / `set` / `list` / `delete` pages** \u2014 rewritten consistently. Output JSON shapes shown explicitly so it\'s clear how to read `.data` and `.items`.\\n- **`get` \\"not found\\" pattern** \u2014 clarified that a missing or expired record routes to `on_complete` with `null` in state (it is **not** a failure). Pairs with a follow-up `matchExpression` using `exists(...)` for the existence check.\\n- **`set` TTL cap** \u2014 documented the 7-day maximum.\\n- **`delete` failure semantics** \u2014 documented that missing/expired keys raise an error and route to `on_failure`.\\n\\n## Fixed\\n\\n- **`func_id` values** \u2014 corrected across Data Storage docs: `get`, `set`, `list`, `delete` (the docs previously suggested `getData`, `setData`, `listData`, `deleteData`, which would not match the bot engine\'s function registry).\\n- **`listData` `total`** \u2014 corrected to reflect the upcoming fix: `total` counts non-expired items **on the current page** (equal to `items.length`), not the raw collection count. The existence-check example uses `total` against the first page."},{"id":"/2026/05/12/data-storage-update-crm","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/12/data-storage-update-crm","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-12-data-storage-update-crm.md","title":"Data Storage Funcs + Chat `updateCrmData` Docs","description":"The YAML reference now covers customer-scoped data storage func nodes and the updateCrmData chat func for persisting crmData, with cross-links from Parse CRM Data and the Data Injection providers table.","date":"2026-05-12T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Data Storage Funcs + Chat `updateCrmData` Docs","date":"2026-05-12T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Subscription Scenarios + Data Storage Docs Polish","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/13/subscription-scenarios-docs-polish"},"nextItem":{"title":"Multi-Select Filters + Mobile Nav Fixes","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/11/filters-mobile-fixes"}},"content":"The YAML reference now covers **customer-scoped data storage** func nodes and the **`updateCrmData`** chat func for persisting `crmData`, with cross-links from Parse CRM Data and the Data Injection providers table.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Data Storage** \u2014 new Func subsection with an overview plus pages for `getData`, `setData`, `listData`, and `deleteData` (`func_type: dataStorage`): collections, keys, TTL, tags, and when to use them instead of `storeValue` or chat `crmData`.\\n- **`updateCrmData`** \u2014 chat-level documentation for merging or replacing `crmData` on the current conversation, including the allowed `mergingMode` values.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **YAML Overview** \u2014 Func table lists `dataStorage` and links the new overview; `chat` row includes `updateCrmData`.\\n- **Data Injection Providers** \u2014 documents `state:node` paths for data-storage node outputs.\\n- **Parse CRM Data** \u2014 points to `updateCrmData` when you need structured writes beyond regex capture."},{"id":"/2026/05/11/filters-mobile-fixes","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/11/filters-mobile-fixes","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-11-filters-mobile-fixes.md","title":"Multi-Select Filters + Mobile Nav Fixes","description":"The Scenario Marketplace tag filter is now multi-select with OR by default and an explicit Match all toggle for AND; the mobile hamburger drawer covers the viewport cleanly on phones; and the landing page no longer churns on 120 Hz Macs.","date":"2026-05-11T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"scenarios","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/scenarios"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Multi-Select Filters + Mobile Nav Fixes","date":"2026-05-11T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["scenarios","site","docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Data Storage Funcs + Chat `updateCrmData` Docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/12/data-storage-update-crm"},"nextItem":{"title":"Transformers \u2014 `get` Examples + API JSON Tip","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/10/transformers-get"}},"content":"The Scenario Marketplace tag filter is now multi-select with OR by default and an explicit **Match all** toggle for AND; the mobile hamburger drawer covers the viewport cleanly on phones; and the landing page no longer churns on 120 Hz Macs.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Multi-select scenario filters** \u2014 pick more than one tag; matching defaults to OR (any selected tag) with a **Match all** checkbox that switches to AND when 2+ tags are active. An active-filters strip below the chip row shows the current selection with `\xd7` removable chips and a one-click **Clear all**.\\n- **Q-AI: Disable External Bot On Pending Chat** \u2014 7th scenario in the Q-AI suite. Fires when a chat is set to pending (e.g. an agent reassigns to another agent during an AI session) and ends the AI handoff cleanly.\\n- **Remember Last Agent on Chat Assigned** \u2014 writes the assigned agent\'s UID and display name into the `ChatsLastAgent` data storage collection so a bot or follow-up scenario can route the next inbound message back to the same agent. Configurable collection name, TTL (max 7 days), and stored fields.\\n- **`data-storage` tag** \u2014 applied to every scenario that reads or writes data storage (the SLA suite, plus the new last-agent scenario), so the marketplace filter can surface them as a group.\\n- **`preserveOriginalAttachmentFilenames`** \u2014 new `sendEmail` parameter. When `true`, email attachments use the original uploaded filename (falling back to the file\'s stored `originalName`, then to the message caption) instead of the chat caption. A new **Attachment filenames** section in the Send Mail page documents the behavior.\\n- **`parseJson` transformer alias** \u2014 accepted as a synonym for `jsonParse`. Both names work identically.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **Filtered scenarios sort alphabetically** \u2014 the marketplace still shuffles for discovery when no filters are applied, but as soon as a search query or tag is active the list switches to alphabetical order.\\n- **Send Mail params layout** \u2014 required and optional parameter lists are now tables with a dedicated **Default** column for optional params, matching the tables used elsewhere on the page.\\n- **Landing page performance** \u2014 removed a hero background animation that was causing scroll lag on 120 Hz Macs. All static visuals (gradient, glow, grid lines) are unchanged.\\n\\n## Fixed\\n\\n- **Sticky navbar** \u2014 the top navigation no longer disappears when scrolling.\\n- **Mobile hamburger drawer** \u2014 multiple bugs resolved on phones: the drawer now has an opaque background instead of bleeding through to the navbar, covers the full viewport width (previously left a strip of the page visible on the right), and its secondary sub-menu panel slides in cleanly over the primary one (previously left a gap on the side)."},{"id":"/2026/05/10/transformers-get","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/10/transformers-get","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-10-transformers-get.md","title":"Transformers \u2014 `get` Examples + API JSON Tip","description":"The Data Injection Transformers page now highlights a practical get pattern for nested values inside JSON returned from API calls, and the crmData example shows a non-ASCII property key.","date":"2026-05-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Transformers \u2014 `get` Examples + API JSON Tip","date":"2026-05-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Multi-Select Filters + Mobile Nav Fixes","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/11/filters-mobile-fixes"},"nextItem":{"title":"Rich Scenario Cards + Shared Markdown","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/04/scenario-markdown"}},"content":"The Data Injection **Transformers** page now highlights a practical `get` pattern for nested values inside JSON returned from API calls, and the `crmData` example shows a non-ASCII property key.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **Transformers (`get`)** \u2014 new tip with a `jsonParse` \u2192 `get(...)` chain for drilling into API response strings, plus a short inline comment on the evaluated result.\\n- **`crmData` example** \u2014 uses a Hebrew field name so dot-path access with `get` reads clearly for localized CRM payloads."},{"id":"/2026/05/04/scenario-markdown","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/04/scenario-markdown","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-04-scenario-markdown.md","title":"Rich Scenario Cards + Shared Markdown","description":"Scenario Marketplace cards now render Markdown so setup notes can link straight into the YAML docs, the Ask AI panel shares the same renderer for consistent navigation, and the YAML Adapters sidebar lists Salesforce before Senzey.","date":"2026-05-04T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"scenarios","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/scenarios"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Rich Scenario Cards + Shared Markdown","date":"2026-05-04T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","scenarios","site","docs"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Transformers \u2014 `get` Examples + API JSON Tip","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/10/transformers-get"},"nextItem":{"title":"Provet Docs + Site Polish","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/03/provet-docs-site-polish"}},"content":"Scenario Marketplace cards now render Markdown so setup notes can link straight into the YAML docs, the Ask AI panel shares the same renderer for consistent navigation, and the YAML Adapters sidebar lists **Salesforce** before **Senzey**.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Shared `Markdown` component** \u2014 GFM rendering with Docusaurus internal links, optional hard line breaks for multi-line snippets, and an optional click handler (used by Ask AI to close the panel when you follow an in-site link).\\n- **Scenario Marketplace** \u2014 each card\u2019s main description and \u201cWhat to configure\u201d items support Markdown: links, emphasis, inline and fenced code, and lists, with tuned styles for body text and inline code.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **Ask AI** \u2014 assistant messages use the shared Markdown layer so link behavior matches the rest of the site.\\n- **Scenario copy** \u2014 broad pass on marketplace text for clearer SLA, Q-AI, Salesforce, Rapid, and cron setup guidance, including cross-links to Data Injection, Notify, and related docs.\\n- **YAML Adapters sidebar** \u2014 Salesforce appears before Senzey in the docs navigation order."},{"id":"/2026/05/03/provet-docs-site-polish","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/03/provet-docs-site-polish","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-03-provet-docs-site-polish.md","title":"Provet Docs + Site Polish","description":"Deeper Provet adapter coverage\u2014including the task editor tool and command behavior\u2014plus navbar, footer, and general UI refinements across the docs site.","date":"2026-05-03T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Provet Docs + Site Polish","date":"2026-05-03T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters","docs","yaml","site"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Rich Scenario Cards + Shared Markdown","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/04/scenario-markdown"},"nextItem":{"title":"Premium Homepage + Theme Polish","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/29/premium-homepage-2"}},"content":"Deeper Provet adapter coverage\u2014including the task editor tool and command behavior\u2014plus navbar, footer, and general UI refinements across the docs site.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **Provet adapter** \u2014 expanded onboarding material, task editor tool usage, and command reference so support teams can wire Provet flows with fewer guess-and-check cycles.\\n- **Navbar and footer** \u2014 layout tweaks for clearer hierarchy and consistency with the rest of the theme.\\n- **General UI** \u2014 small polish passes on shared components and styling for a steadier look in light and dark mode."},{"id":"/2026/04/29/premium-homepage-2","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/29/premium-homepage-2","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-premium-homepage-2.md","title":"Premium Homepage + Theme Polish","description":"A refreshed premium landing experience for Texter Docs, with a redesigned homepage, improved dark/light theme cohesion, and a better navbar experience.","date":"2026-04-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"},{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Premium Homepage + Theme Polish","date":"2026-04-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["site","feature","docs"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Provet Docs + Site Polish","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/05/03/provet-docs-site-polish"},"nextItem":{"title":"Salesforce Adapter Docs Update","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/29/salesforce-adapter-docs-update"}},"content":"A refreshed premium landing experience for Texter Docs, with a redesigned homepage, improved dark/light theme cohesion, and a better navbar experience.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Homepage hero redesign** \u2014 premium landing hero with glow + subtle animated grid background and polished CTA buttons.\\n- **Homepage feature cards** \u2014 new glass/white card grid with icons, hover lift, and clearer hierarchy linking into key docs areas.\\n- **Navbar search** \u2014 search is now available directly in the top navbar.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **Dark + light theme cohesion** \u2014 updated shared theme tokens so switching themes keeps the homepage and cards looking consistent and premium.\\n- **Scenario Marketplace visuals** \u2014 improved card hover shadow to follow the active theme primary color.\\n- **Scenarios header (dark mode)** \u2014 upgraded the hero background to match the new dark aesthetic.\\n\\n## Fixed\\n\\n- **Search bar overlap** \u2014 removed the extra keyboard badge styling that conflicted with the search UI."},{"id":"/2026/04/29/salesforce-adapter-docs-update","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/29/salesforce-adapter-docs-update","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-29-salesforce-adapter-docs-update.md","title":"Salesforce Adapter Docs Update","description":"Expanded the Salesforce adapter documentation with a complete operation reference and clearer onboarding/troubleshooting guidance for support teams.","date":"2026-04-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Salesforce Adapter Docs Update","date":"2026-04-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters","docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Premium Homepage + Theme Polish","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/29/premium-homepage-2"},"nextItem":{"title":"Provet Adapter + Run Bot on Resolve Scenario","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/28/provet-resolve-scenario"}},"content":"Expanded the Salesforce adapter documentation with a complete operation reference and clearer onboarding/troubleshooting guidance for support teams.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Salesforce adapter reference** \u2014 documented `getCustomerDetails`, `openTicket`, `queryFromBot`, and `updateRecord` with YAML usage, params, results, and failure behavior.\\n- **Salesforce API links** \u2014 added direct links to relevant REST API docs for query, create, and update flows.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **Salesforce onboarding guide** \u2014 expanded support setup notes and troubleshooting material for OAuth and object/field discovery.\\n- **Contact-field behavior clarity** \u2014 clarified that `contactObjectCustomFields` replaces the default hardcoded Contact field list in lookups."},{"id":"/2026/04/28/provet-resolve-scenario","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/28/provet-resolve-scenario","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-28-provet-resolve-scenario.md","title":"Provet Adapter + Run Bot on Resolve Scenario","description":"New Provet Cloud adapter docs and a Scenario Marketplace entry that auto-runs the bot when an agent resolves a chat.","date":"2026-04-28T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"scenarios","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/scenarios"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Provet Adapter + Run Bot on Resolve Scenario","date":"2026-04-28T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters","docs","scenarios","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Salesforce Adapter Docs Update","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/29/salesforce-adapter-docs-update"},"nextItem":{"title":"SLA Scenario Suite (Marketplace)","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/28/sla-scenarios"}},"content":"New Provet Cloud adapter docs and a Scenario Marketplace entry that auto-runs the bot when an agent resolves a chat.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Provet adapter** \u2014 documentation for the new Provet Cloud (vet PMS) adapter, including OAuth setup and an onboarding guide for Texter Support.\\n- **Run Bot on Agent Resolve scenario** \u2014 new Scenario Marketplace entry that auto-resumes the bot from a configurable node (e.g. `close_chat`) when an agent resolves a chat.\\n- **Rapid `newOpportunity`** \u2014 `substatus` and `reason` lead fields.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **Request examples** \u2014 switched to `json: true` shorthand instead of manual `Content-Type` headers.\\n- **Check Working Hours** \u2014 legacy deprecation callout moved to the top of the legacy section."},{"id":"/2026/04/28/sla-scenarios","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/28/sla-scenarios","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-28-sla-scenarios.md","title":"SLA Scenario Suite (Marketplace)","description":"Added an SLA scenario suite to the Scenario Marketplace to help track response-time SLAs using a simple per-chat data store record and a default sla label.","date":"2026-04-28T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"scenarios","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/scenarios"},{"inline":true,"label":"marketplace","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/marketplace"},{"inline":true,"label":"sla","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/sla"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/automation"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"SLA Scenario Suite (Marketplace)","date":"2026-04-28T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["scenarios","marketplace","sla","automation"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Provet Adapter + Run Bot on Resolve Scenario","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/28/provet-resolve-scenario"},"nextItem":{"title":"Monday adapter & Zoho `closeTicket` Updates","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/19/monday-zoho"}},"content":"Added an SLA scenario suite to the Scenario Marketplace to help track response-time SLAs using a simple per-chat data store record and a default `sla` label.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **SLA scenario group (tag: `sla`)** \u2014 a dedicated section in the Scenario Marketplace.\\n- **(SLA) Set Item On Incoming Message** \u2014 starts SLA tracking on incoming customer messages (stores timestamp + chat id).\\n- **(SLA) Set Item On Set to pending** \u2014 starts SLA tracking when a chat becomes pending.\\n- **(SLA) Set SLA Label For all Records** \u2014 cron-driven enforcement that applies the `sla` label when the configured threshold is exceeded (default example: 20 minutes, configurable per customer).\\n- **(SLA) Remove Item On Resolve Chat** \u2014 clears tracking + removes the `sla` label when a chat is resolved.\\n- **(SLA) Remove Item On outgoing Message** \u2014 clears tracking + removes the `sla` label when an agent replies."},{"id":"/2026/04/19/monday-zoho","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/19/monday-zoho","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-19-monday-zoho.md","title":"Monday adapter & Zoho `closeTicket` Updates","description":"New Monday.com adapter docs, and an updated Zoho closeTicket that now writes the chat transcript as a Note on the contact.","date":"2026-04-19T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Monday adapter & Zoho `closeTicket` Updates","date":"2026-04-19T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters","docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"SLA Scenario Suite (Marketplace)","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/28/sla-scenarios"},"nextItem":{"title":"Ask AI \u2014 Docs Chat","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/18/ask-ai"}},"content":"New Monday.com adapter docs, and an updated Zoho `closeTicket` that now writes the chat transcript as a Note on the contact.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Monday.com adapter** \u2014 full documentation for the new Monday adapter: `getCustomerDetails`, `createItem`, `updateItem`, `changeStatus`, and `crmGetFields`. Covers the required `crmConfig` (`authToken`, `boardId`, `groupId`, `phoneColumnId`, `statusColumnId`, `workspaceUrl`), column-ID vs. column-title gotchas, per-column-type value formats (status, dropdown, date, phone, email, text), phone-format flags (`useNationalDigits` / `useFullPhoneNumber`), and the `additionalFieldsQuery` / `additionalFieldsVariables` hooks for pulling extra item columns onto `crmData`.\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- **Zoho `closeTicket`** \u2014 now writes the chat transcript as a **Note on the contact** by default (Zoho Create Notes API), using a new stable `crmData.contactId` so the note always lands on the original contact even after later `createRecord` / `updateRecord` calls move `recordId` to another module. The record `PUT` only runs when there\'s something to update (`crmConfig.closeTicketDateField` set, or YAML `params` passed) \u2014 no more spurious updates on agent-resolved chats. New `crmConfig` options: `disableCloseTicketNote` to opt out of the note, and `closeTicketNoteTitle` to override the note-title prefix (default `\u05e9\u05d9\u05d7\u05ea \u05d5\u05d5\u05e6\u05d0\u05e4`)."},{"id":"/2026/04/18/ask-ai","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/18/ask-ai","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-18-ask-ai.md","title":"Ask AI \u2014 Docs Chat","description":"Ask natural-language questions about Texter right inside the docs. A new right-docked chat panel, grounded in the full documentation, is now live on every page.","date":"2026-04-18T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Ask AI \u2014 Docs Chat","date":"2026-04-18T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","site"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Monday adapter & Zoho `closeTicket` Updates","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/19/monday-zoho"},"nextItem":{"title":"Giscus Comments, Template Webhooks, and Passive Marketing Chats","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/14/passive-chats-comments"}},"content":"Ask natural-language questions about Texter right inside the docs. A new right-docked chat panel, grounded in the full documentation, is now live on every page.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Ask AI panel** \u2014 click the \\"Ask AI\\" button in the bottom-right to open a chat that answers questions about YAML, adapters, scenarios, bot flows, and anything else covered in the docs. Works in both English and Hebrew.\\n- **Source citations** \u2014 every answer lists the docs pages it drew from, as clickable links that take you straight to the relevant reference.\\n- **Multi-turn follow-ups** \u2014 the panel remembers your conversation within the session so you can ask follow-ups like \\"and for Zoho?\\" without restating context.\\n- **\\"Ask about this page\\"** \u2014 one-click prompt in the empty state that asks the AI to summarize the page you\'re currently on, the key YAML points to follow, and common mistakes to avoid.\\n- **Prompt suggestions** \u2014 the empty state surfaces three rotating starter questions drawn from a pool of 30, covering data injection, Flows, adapters, prompts, notifies, working hours, and more.\\n- **YAML answers ready to paste** \u2014 YAML code blocks in answers are auto-indented by two spaces so you can paste them directly under an existing key in the bot editor.\\n- **Resizable panel** \u2014 drag the left edge to widen or narrow the panel; your preferred width is remembered across sessions."},{"id":"/2026/04/14/passive-chats-comments","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/14/passive-chats-comments","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-14-passive-chats-comments.md","title":"Giscus Comments, Template Webhooks, and Passive Marketing Chats","description":"New this week: comments on every docs page, three subscribe-to-events templates for template messaging and assignment webhooks, and a scheduled scenario for recovering passive bulk chats.","date":"2026-04-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"scenarios","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/scenarios"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Giscus Comments, Template Webhooks, and Passive Marketing Chats","date":"2026-04-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","scenarios","automation","site"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Ask AI \u2014 Docs Chat","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/18/ask-ai"},"nextItem":{"title":"Google Sheet Adapter","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/10/google-sheet"}},"content":"New this week: comments on every docs page, three subscribe-to-events templates for template messaging and assignment webhooks, and a scheduled scenario for recovering passive bulk chats.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Comments on every page** \u2014 each docs page and scenario card now has a comment section powered by [Giscus](https://giscus.app/), backed by GitHub Discussions. Use it to ask questions, share your own scenario variations, post real-world examples, or discuss edge cases with the community.\\n\\n- **(SUB) Chat Unsubscribed** \u2014 sends a webhook when a chat opts out of template messages (for example when the customer replies with an opt-out keyword such as \\"\u05d4\u05e1\u05e8\\"). Use it to sync suppression lists or update consent in external systems.\\n\\n- **(SUB) Chat Subscribed** \u2014 sends a webhook when a chat subscribes or opts back in to receiving template messages, so you can refresh consent or resume outreach elsewhere.\\n\\n- **(SUB) Chat Assigned** \u2014 sends a webhook when a chat is taken by an agent, including the full chat and a narrowed agent profile (id, crmId, email, displayName, roles) for CRMs, routing tools, or custom backends.\\n\\n- **Handle Passive Marketing Chats** \u2014 cron-triggered scenario that runs once a day, finds BULK chats from the previous day whose last message matched one of your marketing templates, and automatically reassigns them to the sales department (Pending status) while updating the lead\'s status in Rapid CRM. Built for Tyntec provider customers \u2014 see the \\"What to configure\\" section for the expression to use with other WhatsApp providers."},{"id":"/2026/04/10/google-sheet","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/10/google-sheet","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-10-google-sheet.md","title":"Google Sheet Adapter","description":"New Google Sheet adapter docs \u2014 look up customers from a CSV file hosted in Google Drive.","date":"2026-04-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Google Sheet Adapter","date":"2026-04-10T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters","docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Giscus Comments, Template Webhooks, and Passive Marketing Chats","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/14/passive-chats-comments"},"nextItem":{"title":"End-of-Day Closing Message Scenario","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/08/end-of-day-scenario"}},"content":"New Google Sheet adapter docs \u2014 look up customers from a CSV file hosted in Google Drive.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Google Sheet adapter** \u2014 full documentation for `getCustomerDetails` (and its `getCustomerDetailsCSV` alias), including phone-based and ID-based lookups, `filterField`/`filterValue` narrowing, the `crmConfig` field mapping (`customers_csv_*`), how the 10-minute refresh works, how to update the customer list (upload a new CSV \u2014 don\'t edit in place), and supported phone formats"},{"id":"/2026/04/08/end-of-day-scenario","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/08/end-of-day-scenario","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-08-end-of-day-scenario.md","title":"End-of-Day Closing Message Scenario","description":"A new scheduled scenario added to the marketplace for closing out pending chats at the end of the business day.","date":"2026-04-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"scenarios","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/scenarios"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/automation"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"End-of-Day Closing Message Scenario","date":"2026-04-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["scenarios","automation"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Google Sheet Adapter","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/10/google-sheet"},"nextItem":{"title":"Scenario Marketplace","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/07/scenario-marketplace"}},"content":"A new scheduled scenario added to the marketplace for closing out pending chats at the end of the business day.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **End-of-Day Closing Message** \u2014 cron-triggered scenario that finds pending chats with activity in the last ~9 hours and sends a closing message letting customers know they\'ll get a response on the next business day. Configurable per customer via a `ScenariosCustomTriggerCronTask` entry in Nihul (e.g. Sun\u2013Thu at 18:30), excludes chats already labeled `waiting_for_customer`, and sends up to 10 messages concurrently."},{"id":"/2026/04/07/scenario-marketplace","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/07/scenario-marketplace","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-07-scenario-marketplace.md","title":"Scenario Marketplace","description":"Browse, understand, and copy ready-made automation scenarios directly into Texter \u2014 no starting from scratch.","date":"2026-04-07T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"scenarios","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/scenarios"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/automation"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Scenario Marketplace","date":"2026-04-07T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","scenarios","docs","automation"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"End-of-Day Closing Message Scenario","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/08/end-of-day-scenario"},"nextItem":{"title":"Plando Adapter + Docs Fixes","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/02/plando"}},"content":"Browse, understand, and copy ready-made automation scenarios directly into Texter \u2014 no starting from scratch.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Scenario Marketplace** \u2014 new top-level section in the docs site at `/scenarios`\\n- **18 scenarios** across trigger types, action types, and integrations, including:\\n  - Subscribe-to-events templates (incoming messages, chat assigned/resolved, message status, external bot, scheduled, channel health)\\n  - Q-AI suite \u2014 turn on/off AI sessions, forward messages to an AI webhook, end sessions and run a fallback bot\\n  - Salesforce CRM \u2014 create and update service requests on chat events\\n  - Utility \u2014 assign by echo message, label on message error, notify on assignment, forward delivery status\\n- **Tag filtering** \u2014 filter by trigger type, action type, or integration (e.g. `ai-bot`, `salesforce`, `webhook`)\\n- **Search** \u2014 full-text search across scenario name, description, tags, and trigger events\\n- **Per-card flow strip** \u2014 visual trigger \u2192 action icon flow at the top of each card; hover an icon to see its label\\n- **\\"What to configure\\" section** \u2014 collapsible per-scenario guide showing exactly which fields to replace, where they live in the JSON, and whether they\'re required\\n- **Copy JSON** \u2014 one click copies the full scenario JSON to clipboard, ready to paste into Texter\\n- **Randomized ordering** \u2014 cards shuffle on each page load so no scenario is always buried at the bottom"},{"id":"/2026/04/02/plando","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/02/plando","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-02-plando.md","title":"Plando Adapter + Docs Fixes","description":"New Plando CRM adapter docs and a round of fixes and additions across existing pages.","date":"2026-04-02T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Plando Adapter + Docs Fixes","date":"2026-04-02T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters","docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Scenario Marketplace","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/07/scenario-marketplace"},"nextItem":{"title":"Senzey & Lead.IM Adapters + Docs Improvements","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/29/senzey-leadim"}},"content":"New Plando CRM adapter docs and a round of fixes and additions across existing pages.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Plando adapter** \u2014 full documentation for `getCustomerDetails`, `newOpportunity`, `openTicket`/`closeTicket`, and out-of-adapter endpoints (`log_activity`, `upload_contact_file`)\\n- **`log_activity`** \u2014 expanded with all supported API fields including contact identification options, record fields, and response handling\\n- **Send Media** \u2014 added dynamic URL tip (workaround for editor validation when using data injection in `doc:`/`media:`) and a line breaks in captions example\\n\\n## Fixed\\n\\n- **Prompt Text** \u2014 corrected optional param name from `delay_on_complete` to `delay_complete_seconds`"},{"id":"/2026/03/29/senzey-leadim","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/29/senzey-leadim","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-29-senzey-leadim.md","title":"Senzey & Lead.IM Adapters + Docs Improvements","description":"Two new CRM adapter docs, new transformers, and a round of clarity improvements across the docs.","date":"2026-03-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Senzey & Lead.IM Adapters + Docs Improvements","date":"2026-03-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters","docs","yaml"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Plando Adapter + Docs Fixes","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/04/02/plando"},"nextItem":{"title":"Powerlink (Fireberry) CRM Adapter","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/28/powerlink"}},"content":"Two new CRM adapter docs, new transformers, and a round of clarity improvements across the docs.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Senzey adapter** \u2014 full documentation\\n- **Lead.IM adapter** \u2014 full documentation\\n- **New transformers** - `get`, `omit`, `pick`, documented in the Data Injection / Transformers page\\n- **`working_time` schedule table** - allowed days & hours formats documented in `Check Working Hours`\\n- **Diagrams** - added visual diagrams to more complex nodes and flows\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- `Share File` moved to the System functions category (was Utils)\\n- Powerlink, Rapid, Tazman, Zoho adapter pages cleaned up"},{"id":"/2026/03/28/powerlink","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/28/powerlink","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-28-powerlink.md","title":"Powerlink (Fireberry) CRM Adapter","description":"Full documentation for the Powerlink (Fireberry) CRM adapter is now available.","date":"2026-03-28T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Powerlink (Fireberry) CRM Adapter","date":"2026-03-28T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Senzey & Lead.IM Adapters + Docs Improvements","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/29/senzey-leadim"},"nextItem":{"title":"Zoho CRM Adapter","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/27/zoho"}},"content":"Full documentation for the Powerlink (Fireberry) CRM adapter is now available.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Powerlink (Fireberry) CRM adapter** \u2014 full documentation with configuration, field mapping, and YAML examples"},{"id":"/2026/03/27/zoho","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/27/zoho","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-27-zoho.md","title":"Zoho CRM Adapter","description":"Full documentation for the Zoho CRM adapter is now available.","date":"2026-03-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Zoho CRM Adapter","date":"2026-03-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["adapters"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Powerlink (Fireberry) CRM Adapter","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/28/powerlink"},"nextItem":{"title":"Tazman CRM Adapter + Feedback Widget","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/24/tazman-feedback"}},"content":"Full documentation for the Zoho CRM adapter is now available.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Zoho CRM adapter** \u2014 full documentation with field mapping, configuration, and YAML examples\\n\\n## Improved\\n\\n- Feedback widget now shows a success toast after submission\\n- `Keyword Route` node docs clarified\\n- Tazman adapter page cleaned up"},{"id":"/2026/03/24/tazman-feedback","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/24/tazman-feedback","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-24-tazman-feedback.md","title":"Tazman CRM Adapter + Feedback Widget","description":"New Tazman CRM adapter docs, an expanded Markdown examples reference, and a feedback widget on every page.","date":"2026-03-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"},{"inline":true,"label":"site","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/site"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Tazman CRM Adapter + Feedback Widget","date":"2026-03-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","adapters","site"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Zoho CRM Adapter","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/27/zoho"},"nextItem":{"title":"Documentation Site Live \u2014 Full YAML Reference + Rapid Adapter","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/22/initial-launch"}},"content":"New Tazman CRM adapter docs, an expanded Markdown examples reference, and a feedback widget on every page.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n- **Tazman CRM adapter** \u2014 full documentation with configuration examples\\n- **Feedback widget** \u2014 appears on every page, lets users report issues or request clarification. Submissions open tasks for the Texter team\\n- **Markdown Examples page** \u2014 greatly expanded with detailed examples covering all supported syntax\\n\\n## Fixed\\n\\n- Feedback form submit button is now disabled until all required fields are filled\\n- Various clarifications and corrections in Rapid adapter docs"},{"id":"/2026/03/22/initial-launch","metadata":{"permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/22/initial-launch","source":"@site/blog/2026-03-22-initial-launch.md","title":"Documentation Site Live \u2014 Full YAML Reference + Rapid Adapter","description":"The Texter documentation site is now live with complete YAML bot configuration reference and the first CRM adapter docs.","date":"2026-03-22T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"feature","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/feature"},{"inline":true,"label":"docs","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/docs"},{"inline":true,"label":"yaml","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/yaml"},{"inline":true,"label":"adapters","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/tags/adapters"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Documentation Site Live \u2014 Full YAML Reference + Rapid Adapter","date":"2026-03-22T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["feature","docs","yaml","adapters"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Tazman CRM Adapter + Feedback Widget","permalink":"/texterdocs/changelog/2026/03/24/tazman-feedback"}},"content":"The Texter documentation site is now live with complete YAML bot configuration reference and the first CRM adapter docs.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Added\\n\\n**YAML Node Types**\\n- `Choice` and `Text` prompt nodes\\n- `Notify` and `Send Media` notify nodes\\n- `WhatsApp Flow` node\\n- System functions: `Bot State Split`, `Check Working Hours`, `Format Date`, `Keyword Route`, `Match Expression`, `Noop`, `Parse CRM Data`, `Request`, `Send Mail`, `Send Webhook`, `Set Language`, `Store Value`, `Switch Node`\\n- Chat functions: `Add Label`, `External Bot`, `Sensitive Session`\\n- Utility functions: `Match Values`, `Random Code`, `Share File`\\n\\n**Data Injection**\\n- YAML Overview\\n- Data Injection: Overview, Legacy Syntax, Providers, and Transformers\\n- Bot Configuration reference\\n\\n**Adapters**\\n- Adapters section with Overview page\\n- Full Rapid CRM adapter documentation\\n\\n**Site**\\n- Full-text local search\\n- Last updated timestamps on every page"}]}}')}}]);